				<listApp/>
			</div>
			<div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
				<p><!--english translation here--></p>
			</div>
			<div type="commentary">
				<p>The &lt;T&gt; of <foreign>hraTṁ</foreign> has a right-pointing final stroke unlike the down-pointing final stroke of the &lt;T&gt; of the previous akṣara. Could it be a &lt;N&gt;?</p>
			</div>
			<div type="bibliography">
				<!--Myint Aung 1978: 2. — Sein Maung U 1981: 5; Sein Maung Oo 1989: 138. — Naing Zaw 2011: 87.-->
				<!--[Todo: markup citedRange elements if necessary]-->
				<p>First mentioned in a newspaper article, <bibl><ptr target="bib:MyintAung1978_01"/><citedRange>2</citedRange></bibl>, which describes a silver bowl with a line of Pyu inscription on its rim. Probably one of the two silver bowls mentioned by <bibl><ptr target="bib:SeinMaungOo1981"/><citedRange>5</citedRange></bibl>. Re-edited here from published and our own photographs.</p>
				<listBibl type="primary"><bibl><ptr target="bib:CPI2018_01"/><citedRange unit="item">DHARMA_INSPYU00038</citedRange></bibl></listBibl><listBibl type="secondary">
